div.p:
Which ſaid complaints of theirs (being ſo juſt and true) may not be paſſed over in ſilence, but ſome fit remedies applied for their better incouragement according to the Lawes of this Kingdome: the ſaid Office of Sheriffe being an Office of high truſt and authority, both for the ſervice of the King and Common-wealth;
The ſheriffe anciently ſtiled Firmarius & cu ſtos Cem.
                   and the Sheriff being anciently ſtiled Firmarius & cuſtos Cō.
